`handle_item/4` function.

Implement the private `handle_item/4` function, `handle_item(item, line, idx, acc)`.
It receives an already-built `item` map (`%{name: ..., description: ..., tags: ...}`),
the trailing-whitespace-trimmed `line` string, its 1-indexed `idx`, and the running
accumulator `acc` (which holds `:cats`, `:current`, `:errors`, and `:seen`).

Its job is to attach the item to the currently open category — or to report it —
by dispatching on `acc.current`:

- When `acc.current` is a category node (a map `%{category: ..., items: [...]}`),
  prepend `item` to that node's `items` list (items are accumulated in reverse and
  reversed on flush) and return the updated `acc`.
- When `acc.current` is `:suppressed` (the current section belongs to a duplicate
  category), silently ignore the item — return `acc` unchanged, adding no error.
- When `acc.current` is `nil` (no category has been opened yet), the item is an
  orphan: record an `:orphan_item` error for this line via `add_error/4` and discard
  the item.

